# Learned Patterns: Mcp

*Auto-generated by Hippocampus MOS from 3 error patterns in hippocampus.*
*Last updated: 2026-03-23 21:26*

## Pattern 1

**BUG: MCP stdio transport uses newline-delimited JSON, NOT Content-Length framing like LSP. CAUSE: copied LSP pattern blindly. FIX: changed to bufio.Scanner + json.Marshal + newline. FILE: internal/adapter/mcp/server.go**


## Pattern 2

The MCP tools not appearing in Cursor was caused by: Cursor caching old tool definitions from a previous hippocampus.exe binary. This led to hours of debugging. Fixed: always build to bin/ directory and fully restart Cursor after each rebuild. Prevented future issues by adding the correct binary path to mcp.json.

## Pattern 3

MCP transport was using Content-Length framing (LSP-style) but MCP stdio spec requires newline-delimited JSON. Fixed in internal/adapter/mcp/server.go: replaced bufio.Reader+readMessage with bufio.Scanner, send() now writes JSON+newline instead of Content-Length header. This was the root cause of Cursor not being able to connect to Hippocampus.

